==English==
===Etymology===
Blend of [[man]] and [[animal]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
#{{slang}} A [[fanciful]] [[life form]] that is part [[human]] and part [[beast]]; a [[creature]] recognizable as human but possessing physical or [[primitive]] behavioral characteristics that are exclusive to animals.
#*'''2006''' Feb. 1, Paul Z. Myers, ''Pharyngula'', ScienceBlogs
#*:''President panders to anti-'''manimal''' lobby! Dr Moreau flees country in rage!''
#*'''2006''' Feb. 4, Charlie Pierce, ''Wait Wait... Don't Tell Me!'', National Public Radio
#*:''Two years ago we were going to Mars, and that sort of didn't happen...and now there's, like, '''manimal'''.''
#{{slang}} A usually male individual compared to such a creature, esp. an [[unkempt]] and [[uncivilized]], or strong and sexually agressive person.

